The paper is about using machine learning to bias the components of programs in multidimensional genetic programming, which is a subfield of genetic programming (GP). Therefore, cs.GP is the most likely category. The paper also discusses the use of heuristic search and the disentangling of factors of variation, which are topics that are relevant to machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG and cs.AI). The paper also presents results on regression problems, which are commonly studied in neural networks and other machine learning models (cs.NE). Finally, the paper proposes operators to improve the evolutionary process, which is relevant to systems and control (cs.SY).
